[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating class loading behavior**\n\nThe target behavior requires loading a class in an isolated classloader after the image build. There’s a warning not to use this dynamic-class-loading pattern for certain scenarios like ordinary reflection or serialization. In a JVM context, loading a second copy of a specific jar via URLClassLoader could mean that call sites might still be covered. I’ll need to locate the jar and find the source URL for certain code while considering parenting in the classloader context. Is a child-first loading strategy best?\n\n**Exploring reflection and classloading**\n\nIf the URLClassLoader has a null parent, it will load directly from the jar. Since all the org.bouncycastle classes are in the same jar, I’m thinking about how to call a public method via reflection. The rule here is to avoid direct reflection unless required by a public API. Using dynamic loading and invoking a method involves reflection, likely using methods like `Class.forName` and `getMethod`. I’ll also consider generating test reflection calls — maybe it's not an issue? Tests could filter out user code.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0c3522f9ffbdd0db016a268daa9b5081948b0222998d91dc37\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJo28l4crHTBBMaVrtro-gZe8WhFJOTvAYaiIMc2ezfihFfTS7HrLdnTrvyDbhl4KN3kwYozsFbp05_wF6W0WHdEC6MyrN3YhbNU4iRVNoFArEaMUKtz6uzBVrcZBRd17Ko9TYnxBuWWU1LckVAdb0PKpoQz9Zd39RkLHJQAZkJgY9QO0JVyN4OyiwKnGznreOXIYrPcdecDfpnkKhAtdjdQZRAntiEUO3aqJUJR96-KqjpkLYbEAAJoUpCsRwVYVP3mRUyRHKCNZdhrGfBJfOjZExQ4KupxY1XfUBsKWZp-a1LQj8VVl5QLuA1szMKDJDeMMxinLMVRBPk4biHSFdcL2ubQ0GOfn3Kfhf7VNKTfYVOjlE6NsPaobrOlvRB3ADsRTs6POtUjcXeAPyRSylOwHTqkRBJzTwvJIL9TUxNeNPUGPoTecYoEDqGNZXZYm-fT9Zs_LOsQttA-ionJNn9y317m75rz5fXyecsMYEfeHspyL9Bu1k6g1znK5lZvdRfwrworKxPsHf4Mo1eeKJD84HspLr-_JgKPrqwx6ueX_4YN8f7LIklsFPX0lnCsv9-I7OtmBTW_nAZI2uP4dloFiJWyVE2E2iI